          "file": "ghost/core/core/server/services/email-service/DomainWarmingService.ts",
          "line": 121,
          "severity": "medium",
          "category": "correctness",
          "message": "The new high-volume cap logic uses `lastCount >= WARMUP_SCALING_TABLE.highVolume.threshold` (>= 400k) but the thresholds loop uses `lastCount < threshold.limit` (strict less than). This creates a gap: when `lastCount` is exactly 400,000, the high-volume block returns a value, but the thresholds array also has a limit of 400,000 with scale 2. The thresholds loop will never match 400,000 because of the strict `<`, so the high-volume block is the only handler. However, the comment says 'thresholds cover all cases up to highVolume.threshold', but the thresholds array includes 400,000 as a limit, which is now unreachable. This is confusing and could lead to unexpected scaling if the high-volume block is ever removed or modified.",
          "suggestion": "Either remove the 400,000 entry from the thresholds array (since it is now handled by the high-volume block) or change the high-volume condition to `lastCount > WARMUP_SCALING_TABLE.highVolume.threshold` to avoid overlap and make the intent clear.",
